Tic-Tac-Toe with Tree Implementation (C++)
📌 Description
This project implements a Tic-Tac-Toe game in C++ using a tree-based approach to store game states. It enhances understanding of data structures and algorithms (DSA) by utilizing binary trees to track board configurations.

✨ Features
Tree-based storage of game states
Manual player input (two-player mode)
Winner detection and draw conditions
Command-line interface (CLI)
🛠 Installation
Clone the repository:
sh
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/tic-tac-toe-tree.git
cd tic-tac-toe-tree
Compile the C++ code:
sh
Copy
Edit
g++ tic_tac_toe.cpp -o tic_tac_toe
Run the game:
sh
Copy
Edit
./tic_tac_toe
🎮 How to Play
Players take turns marking X and O on a 3x3 board.
The game tree stores board states after each move.
The game automatically detects winners or a draw.
🖥 Example Board Input
Copy
Edit
 1 | 2 | 3  
 4 | 5 | 6  
 7 | 8 | 9  
Players enter numbers 1-9 to place their mark on the board.

